To: ois-members@maillist.ox.ac.uk
Reply-To: essay-award@oxfordindiasociety.org.uk
Subject: Oxford India Society Essay Award 2014-15 (200 GBP, deadline 26 Jan 2015)

Dear members,

Oxford India Society invites students of University of Oxford to submit
essays on any matter relating to contemporary India. This award is to
encourage students to articulate and share their ideas about India.
  
Essays should be no longer than 5000 words in length and should be written
in English.  The winning entry will be awarded 200 GBP, and the top 5
entries will be published on the Oxford India policy blog:
http://policyblog.oxfordindiasociety.org.uk/.
   
Entries must be sent to
 essay-award@oxfordindiasociety.org.uk
latest by 26 January 2015.  The results will be announced by the close of
Hilary Term 2015. 

Regards
Team OIS
